{
  "texts": [
    "This work performs an empirical study on five recent LLMs, including GPT-3.",
    "5 [43], LLaMA-33B/13B/7B [50], and CodeGen [41], for automated code translation task and compare their performance with the three state-of-the-art learning-based transpilers, including TransCoder [46], TransCoder-IR [48], and TransCoder-ST [47].",
    "We first manually clean the widelyused code translation dataset released by Roziere et al. [46] due to many errors and inconsistencies among its parallel corpus.",
    "Based on the cleaned dataset, we evaluate the above models under the metrics of Computational Accuracy (CA) and Exact Match Accuracy (EM Acc), where four settings of translation datasets (i.e., C++ to Java, Java to C++, C++ to Python, and Python to C++) are involved in this empirical study.",
    "Results demonstrate certain LLMs have outperformed state-of-the-art learning-based transpilers, and LLMs with more parameters tend to carry more powerful translation capabilities, showing that automated code translation with LLMs is promising."
  ]
}